column632: Looking for a lease takeover for a 1 bedroom/1 bathroom house located in a safe and quiet neighborhood, only 2min bike ride from campus. Start date for take over would be around June 15th (date is negotiable) and would extend for the entire 2024-2025 school year ending on August 31, 2025. The rent would be $1450 until August 2024 and then raise to $1650 for the remainder of the lease.The house is part of a duplex and has a front yard, garage, and drive way. It is very close to campus and a walking distance from Downtown Davis and the Farmer's Market. Small pets allowed, there are 2 pet deposits included in the take over. The living room has a door, so the space can be used as a second bedroom or a living room. Please message with any inquiries and questions!
I’m a PhD (computer science) UCD alumni. I’m looking for a summer sublease for a furnished room within walking distance of downtown Davis -for a low rent. Message me please.

🚨 SINGLE ROOM AVAILABLE 🚨

I’m looking for a female undergrad or grad student to take over my lease OR sublease. The room is available now. May 1st works too. 🙏🏻

It’s a FURNISHED private room with a shared bath in a 3bdrm 2.5 bath townhouse. 

No doubles or couples — pet friendly though!!

Comes with a full-sized mattress and side desk. 

Housemates are all female undergrad students and are incredible, reasonable, and friendly.

✅ Rent: $1062/month
✅ Wifi: $11
✅ PG&E: usually $36/month
✅ Gas stove
✅ Renewed unit with new carpet 
✅ 6 min from campus 
✅ 7 min from the ARC
✅ 6 min from Downtown Davis
✅ Bus line right out front 

Lease ends August 31st with option to renew ✌️

If you’re looking for amazing housemates and a a drama-free home, just shoot me a DM. 🙏🏻

Good afternoon everyone,
Due to some last minute changes I am looking to fill the downstairs bedroom in a 3 bed/ 2 bath apartment at Parque Plaza Davis for the upcoming lease.

The downstairs room is 12'6"x15'6.  This room will essentially have their own bathroom. The rent for this room will be $590. This room also has direct access to the back patio. The patio can be accessed from outside through a side gate. The furniture will be removed before moving in, unless you wish to keep them.

Housemate requirements: Respectful and willing to share common area. Cleans up after themselves in the common area to a reasonable degree. No smoking inside the apartment. 

Utilities:
Electricity ~ $30 per person
Internet ~ $22 (subject to change if we want faster speeds)

Location-wise, the apartment is very close to a gas station and a grocery store, as well as multiple restaurants. The apartment is also within easy walking distance of a unitrans bus line stop. Only a few minutes from the CA-113 freeway and 5 minutes from the UC Davis campus by car. It is around 10 minutes away from the UC Davis campus by bike.

Message if interested alongside any questions you may have.

Hi everyone, I’m moving to a new apartment and am looking for a female housemate (undergrad or grad is okay) to take over my lease starting May 1st, 2024. 

It’s a FURNISHED private room with a shared bath in a 3bdrm 2.5 bath townhouse. 

Comes with a full-sized mattress and side desk. 

Housemates are all female undergrad students and are incredible, reasonable, and friendly.

✅ Rent: $1062/month
✅ Wifi: $11

Huge, 15' x 25' bright and clean 3rd floor suite w/12' high ceiling, equipped w/ private full bath, walk-in closet, storage closet and shuttered windows, in this new (only 6 years old), contemporary, spacious and immaculate 3 story home located on a private corner lot at the famous 'The Cannery' district in Davis, CA

Located less than 2 miles from downtown Davis and UCD campus; 'The Cannery' is the upscale and well-developed community. Home is equipped with modern conveniences:

- Distributed, central A/C & Heating system: independantly-controlled, 4 different temp zones 
- Updated kitchen equipped with stainless steel appliances including 27 cu ft Kitchenaid fridge
- In-house laundry w/ Samsung heavy-duty front loading washer & dryer
- Dining/living area w/ laminate flooring
- Atached 2-car garage (1 spot) w/ tankless water-heater and solar panels (reduced utility cost)

Available 09/01/24 for a 12-month lease

Rent is $1300/mo + 1/n Utilities (Elect/Gas + H2O + Garbage) w/ $1300 security deposit; includes free 300 Mbps internet. 
It also includes access to the Cannery community pool and clubhouse (Ranch House and Farm House): visit: https://www.livecannerydavis.com for details

-No drugs, no pets, no smoking and no loud party please

**Welcome to Upscale Living in Davis' Exclusive Cannery Community**

Discover the epitome of comfort and convenience in our modern, three-story townhouse, nestled in the heart of the newly developed Cannery community. Owned by a UC Davis alum who values flexibility and quality living, this property offers a seamless move-in experience for those seeking a high-standard lifestyle close to campus.

·  - Modern Design: A spacious 3 bed / 3.5 bath layout ensures privacy and comfort. Each room boasts its own private bathroom, marrying convenience with luxury.

·  - Fully Furnished: Our turn-key solution features tastefully furnished rooms, complete with high-quality beds, work desks, bookshelves, and state-of-the-art entertainment systems, including a 55” 4K HDR TV and stereo sound system. Just bring your luggage and feel at home instantly.

·  - Energy Efficiency: Enjoy the benefits of top-tier insulation and solar panels, significantly reducing your energy bills while ensuring year-round comfort.

Ideal for those who appreciate extra space and comfort. Price: $1400/month for single occupancy. $1500/month for double occupancy.

 $1,100/month. The lease term is from 09/01/2024 to 08/31/2025. The rent includes water, garbage, and gardener. Internet fee is $25/ month. Gas and electricity bills will be split among tenants. There are 2 refrigerators, washer, dryer to share among housemates. Looking for a very easy-going, friendly, kind, and responsible mature who would be happy to share the house with others. There will be 3 male UCD students living in the house next school year. Please no drinking, drugs, smoking, parties, or pets. Please call or text me to have a walk-through at 408-458-6275.

Hi everyone,

My partner and I are looking for 2 COVID-conscious people (who still mask indoors) to join our lease renewal for the 2024-25 school year (8/1/2024-7/31/2025). The lease is for a 4br/2ba house located along the green belt near the intersection of F Street and Covell in North/Central Davis. The house is about a 15-minute bike ride from campus and a 5-10 minute drive from both Save Mart and Grocery Outlet.

The larger room is $875/month and the smaller room is $725. You would be sharing the hallway bathroom with one person. The shared spaces are furnished, but the rooms will not be. We will split the city bill, PG&E, and wifi equally - the city bill and PG&E put together usually equal $75-100 per person per month, and the wifi is $18.50 per person per month. The application fee for property management is $45. Since this is a lease renewal, we are still figuring out how to transfer the deposit per person, but the deposit would be around one month's rent per person.

My partner and I are both PhD students at UC Davis. We are abolitionists, pro-Palestine, queer, and 420/alcohol friendly. We like to cook and share our food, so if you'd like to do meals communally, we can definitely discuss further, but if not, no pressure. We also like to spend time in the backyard and occasionally have folks over for dinner. Overall, we would like to find housemates who are responsible and communicative, willing to split and do the household chores on a weekly basis, and willing to maintain clean and organized public areas.

Additional details:
- driveway or easy street parking
- bike racks in the garage
- in-unit washer/dryer
- 2 fridges
- central heating/AC
- enclosed backyard with 2 garden boxes
- no pets

If this sounds like it would be a good fit for you, please message us back so we can meet, discuss further, and give you a tour of the house.

2x2 Townhouse on the Individual Lease Program (single room or whole unit) available for Fall 2024– Right down the street from UC Davis!

**Pricing by the bedroom! Single room $1,740 or a shared room $895/ person— housemate matching available!

The rental price includes the following benefits: 

-Free high speed internet of up to 800 mbps 
-Free city utilities (water, sewage, trash)
-Free membership to the Sundance Care Program (care packages -delivered monthly, free printing, rent raffle monthly, etc) 
-Free printing/ coffee station
-Free uncovered parking

column632: Hello UC Davis! 2 bedroom apt for rent in Woodland upstairs unit $1750 very small complex. Good credit and rental history. Please message me for more information.

Hi everyone, I’m moving in with my fiancé and am looking for a female housemate to take over my lease starting April 1st, 2024. 

It’s a private room with a shared bath in a 3bdrm 2.5 bath townhouse. 

Housemates are all female undergrad students and are incredible, reasonable, and friendly.

✅ Rent: $1062/month
✅ Wifi: $11
✅ PG&E: usually $36/month
✅ Gas stove
✅ Renewed unit with new carpet 
✅ 6 min from campus 
✅ 7 min from the ARC
✅ 6 min from Downtown Davis
✅ Bus line right out front 

Lease ends August 31st with option to renew ✌️

If you want to know more, just shoot me a DM. 🙏🏻
